1. Dragonball can be rephrased as "Dragon Ball" to emphasize the separation between the words. This change highlights the mythical and powerful nature of the dragon, while also acknowledging the significance of the ball in the story.

2. Another way to rewrite Dragonball is by using "Dragon Ball" as two separate words. This alteration helps to clarify the concept of a dragon and a ball, which are both integral elements in the series. By separating the words, the title becomes more descriptive and evocative.

3. To present a different version of Dragonball, it can be transformed into "Dragon Orb." This modification maintains the essence of the original title while adding a touch of mystery and intrigue. The term "orb" suggests a mystical object, enhancing the fantastical elements of the story.

